('6808', '2', 'To prepare fish, heat canola oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle fish evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('6808', '3', 'Add fish to pan. cook 3 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness. Arrange 1 cup greens on each of 4 plates. Top each serving with 1 fish fillet. drizzle with 2 tablespoons dressing.'),
('6810', '1', 'Toss together the coconut, flour and Creole seasoning in a bowl.  In a separate bowl, toss the tilapia with the cornstarch, and shake off the excess.'),
('6810', '2', 'Pour the egg substitute into a separate bowl, and dip the fillets in the egg.  Press fillets in the coconut mixture coating all sides.'),
